docs.abstract: A study of 25 states provides a rare glimpse of the stark disparities between what private insurers and the federal government paid for inpatient and outpatient care.
docs.snippet: A study of 25 states provides a rare glimpse of the stark disparities between what private insurers and the federal government paid for inpatient and outpatient care.
docs.lead_paragraph: In Indiana, a local hospital system, Parkview Health, charged private insurance companies about four times what the federal Medicare program paid for the same care, according to a study of hospital prices in 25 states released on Thursday by the nonprofit RAND Corp.

headline.main: Many Hospitals Charge Double or Even Triple What Medicare Would Pay
headline.print_headline: Study Finds ‘Eye-Opening’ Gap in Hospital Bills

docs.abstract: Anthem may save money simply by announcing its policy, even if it is never enforced.
docs.snippet: Anthem may save money simply by announcing its policy, even if it is never enforced.
docs.lead_paragraph: The health insurer Anthem is coming under intense criticism for denying claims for emergency room visits it has deemed unwarranted. A new congressional report suggests Anthem has effectively reversed that policy, even as it is being hit with a new lawsuit about it from doctors.

headline.main: A Health Insurer Tells Patients It Won’t Pay Their E.R. Bills, but Then Pays Them Anyway
headline.print_headline: Anthem Pays E.R. Visits It Once Said It Wouldn’t

byline.original: By Margot Sanger-Katz and Reed Abelson
